Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.68,0:00:15.38,Default,Organization Member,0,0,0,,We've been waiting for you, Briar Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.35,0:00:23.21,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.71,0:00:27.22,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Your garden is as lovely as ever, Shopkeeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.25,0:00:29.22,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,It is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.97,0:00:34.22,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,With proper watering, pruning, \Nand consistent care,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.99,0:00:39.37,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,we can ensure that the world \Nremains a beautiful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:43.16,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Welcome, Briar Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.93,0:00:46.55,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,The heather smells so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:50.30,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,The leaves of the spindle tree \Nalso look lovely right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.30,0:00:51.04,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.03,0:00:53.49,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.31,0:01:02.69,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Goodness, that startled me!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.76,0:01:04.75,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.03,0:01:08.51,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I was worried that the family life\Nmight've dulled your instincts,{I feared that your skills may have \Ndulled since you obtained a family...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.73,0:01:10.51,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,but they seem as honed as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.51,0:01:13.51,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Now I can let you serve our \Nnext customer without worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:17.54,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Of course! I am ready to end \Nany evildoer at any time!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.56,0:01:21.02,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,How reassuring. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.02,0:01:24.27,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,This time, you'll be protecting the client. {K: could use "escort" here, e.g. "escorting someone"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.53,0:01:25.61,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Protecting?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.98,0:01:27.03,Default,opsync,0,0,0,,{opsync}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:02.83,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Have you heard of the Gretcher family?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:08.29,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,For generations, they've been a powerful force\Nin maintaining this country's underworld. {K:: note, "handling" here has a positive nuance, as in they played a big role in maintaining order in the underworld}
Comment: 0,0:03:05.65,0:03:08.29,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,in handling this country's underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.65,0:03:14.23,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,A little while back, the boss and his two sons\Nwere killed in an internal dispute. {K:: "his children" is lit. "his two sons", might be worth specifying the gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.23,0:03:16.80,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,The only Gretchers to survive the incident{The only ones of the Gretcher \Nfamily who survived...}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.60,0:03:20.30,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,were Olka Gretcher and her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.30,0:03:23.00,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,She's being kept in a safehouse for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:26.00,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,But the man who took over their \Norganization, Leonardo Hapoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.00,0:03:28.54,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,is desperately trying to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.54,0:03:30.35,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,He's put a bounty on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.82,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,so now she's the target of every hitman\N in the country.{and every hitman in the country \Nand beyond is on the move.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.65,0:03:39.68,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,We've decided that having her seek asylum \Nin another country is her best option.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.68,0:03:41.33,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,She'll escape by sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.63,0:03:43.88,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,To make sure she isn't caught by the coastal guard,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.88,0:03:49.33,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,she'll take a regular passenger cruise\Nand rendezvous with our allies.{she will go out to sea on a normal passenger ship}
Comment: 0,0:03:46.64,0:03:49.33,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,and then rendezvous with another ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.33,0:03:54.59,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I'd like you to stay by her side \Nuntil she's handed over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.10,0:03:58.80,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Protecting a high-level mafia member\N from an army of trained hitmen?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:03.07,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,In an ideal world, \Nthe odds wouldn't be so stacked against her,{Of course, it would be ideal if \Nshe doesn't run into the enemy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.07,0:04:05.06,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,but we just want to play it safe.{but now we need someone to protect her.}{"but the truth is that..."}{K:: lit. is "But we want to play it safe (just in case)." but fine as-is}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:09.47,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,The Gretcher family boss was a man \NI owe a debt of gratitude to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:11.58,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I'd greatly appreciate if you took this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.58,0:04:12.45,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.45,0:04:15.28,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Well, what about my job at city hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:18.08,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Also, if I'm going to be gone for a couple of days,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:20.66,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I have to think of an excuse to give my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:23.31,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,You needn't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.31,0:04:27.98,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I've devised a plan that allows you to do this \Nunder the guise of your civil servant work.{I've devised a plan so you could go on this mission}
Comment: 0,0:04:25.69,0:04:27.98,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,as a part of your job as a civil servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.98,0:04:30.67,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Your manager will fill you in\N on the details later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:34.43,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I knew I could count on you, Briar Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.43,0:04:37.67,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Continue the fight to keep the world \Na beautiful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.95,0:04:41.25,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,A-All right. I'll give it my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.39,0:04:51.20,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}This'll be one of my biggest jobs in a while.{It's been a while since I've had a job.} {K: misTL imo. she's been doing assassin work, she just hasn't had any big jobs in quite a while. consider "My first high-profile job in a while..." or similar}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.20,0:04:52.79,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.08,0:04:56.17,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.17,0:04:57.15,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.42,0:05:01.89,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I haven't seen you take this train before!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.89,0:05:04.62,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah... I just got back \Nfrom a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.62,0:05:06.84,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}Actually, I was arresting \Na political dissident.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:09.47,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Well, good work. \NWould you like to join us for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.47,0:05:10.33,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Can I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.09,0:05:13.45,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Actually, I don't think I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.45,0:05:16.74,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Loidy's at your place, \Nand I've still got some work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.74,0:05:18.42,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like sorting through transcripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:21.20,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Goodness, are you ever going to get along with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:22.49,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.49,0:05:24.27,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Have you been eating properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.27,0:05:26.43,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Make sure you're not leaving \Nyour socks lying around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.59,0:05:30.43,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor, I'm not a kid anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:33.42,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.42,0:05:34.78,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:37.59,Default,Train announcer,0,0,0,,{\an8}Now stopping at Fogue Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.88,0:05:40.04,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,I can't keep clinging to you forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:39.19,Default,Train announcer,0,0,0,,{\an8}Fogue Square.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.19,0:05:41.68,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Though I just did the other day...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.20,0:05:46.44,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,It's you who should start relying \Non me if anything ever happens.{And actually, you should rely on \Nme if anything ever happens.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.44,0:05:49.07,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'd happily put an end to Loidy! {K: consider immediately -> gladly/happily}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:50.13,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:05:59.19,Default,Yuri,0,0,0,,Yor!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:04.51,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I guess Yuri's all grown up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.16,0:06:06.51,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of course he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.02,0:06:10.28,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}He has a proper job,\Nand he's making a living on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.94,0:06:13.05,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}He doesn't need my help anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.13,0:06:19.57,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is there any real reason\NI need to continue my job as a killer?{Is there actually any reason why \NI need to continue my job as a killer?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:23.82,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Too bad! Yer seventh-place prize, one brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.82,0:06:24.90,Default,Customer A,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:28.67,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Come on up fer a chance to win big  \Nat our biannual grand raffle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.67,0:06:31.95,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Fer just 30 dalc, ya get a chance\Nat winnin' one of these amazin' prizes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:33.11,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,First prize, believe it or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.11,0:06:36.46,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,is two tickets fer that luxury cruise \Neveryone's buzzin' about lately!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.88,0:06:38.96,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Keep those tickets comin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.98,0:06:40.87,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.66,0:06:45.46,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I'm gonna get on that boat \Nand have a big adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.46,0:06:46.97,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,I see. How valiant of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.42,0:06:50.33,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Now gimme that raffle ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.33,0:06:52.15,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Just remember, we only have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.71,0:06:56.06,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,That sucks! \NHere's yer sixth-place premium brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:59.95,Default,Customer B,0,0,0,,What the hell, man? \NIs there even a winning ticket in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.95,0:07:02.90,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,First place is still up for grabs, y'all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.03,0:07:05.36,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ya bunch of fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:08.31,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yer all dropping money on \Na prize yer not gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.36,0:07:13.54,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}That cruise is as good as mine. \NI've made sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.54,0:07:16.78,Default,Cindy,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yeah, yeah, I know. \NI just have to pretend we're strangers.{We're supposed to act like strangers.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.79,0:07:20.88,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}The first-place ticket is stuck\N to the top of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.88,0:07:23.14,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}None of ya are gettin' it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.14,0:07:25.21,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}Call it an employee benefit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:28.93,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}Feelin' excited, Cindy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.45,0:07:33.14,Default,Cindy,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't even like cruises, \Nbut a free trip's a free trip I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:33.14,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\an8}Aw, too bad! Here's your \Nfifth-place gold brush!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:36.78,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Oh? Are you gonna be our lucky little lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.78,0:07:39.15,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Here you go. Hope you win!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.44,0:07:42.36,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}Go on and get yer losin' ticket, pipsqueak.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.36,0:07:45.13,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,{\i1}First place is goin'\Nto that nice lady behind ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.16,0:07:54.92,Default,Employee A,0,0,0,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:57.34,Default,Employee B,0,0,0,,We have a winner!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:58.77,Alt,Employee A,0,0,0,,How the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.19,0:08:05.34,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'm home, Loid and Anya!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.00,0:08:07.55,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Look at this, Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.30,0:08:10.55,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I won a fancy boat trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.55,0:08:11.33,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.33,0:08:14.99,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,She managed to win first prize \Nat a department store's raffle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.99,0:08:15.89,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,My, that's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.27,0:08:19.07,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}Too amazing. It's making me \Nwonder if it's some sort of trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.07,0:08:21.40,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,{\i1}Daddy is suspicious of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.73,0:08:24.84,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Since there are two tickets, \Nwhy don't you go with her, Yor?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.84,0:08:26.03,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,I still have to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.03,0:08:28.73,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,I'm so excited! I've never been to the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.73,0:08:30.29,Default,Bond,0,0,0,,Borf, borf!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:31.52,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,You have to stay home, Bond.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.52,0:08:32.03,Default,Bond,0,0,0,,Borf!{if this one is too short, just make it end at the start of the next line -Nyarthur}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:35.69,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,A trip on the {\i1}Princess Lorelei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.69,0:08:38.33,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,This is the same ship \NI'm going to be on for my work trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.33,0:08:39.32,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:42.20,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,And it's the exact ship \Nthat's leaving on Friday...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.20,0:08:43.56,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,You're going on a work trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.56,0:08:44.36,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:47.80,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Um... the city is trying to attract \Na famous grocery chain,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.80,0:08:50.13,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,and I'm supposed to be entertaining a VIP.{so I'm entertaining someone \Nvery important from there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.13,0:08:53.91,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Ah, must be a modern form of urban planning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.91,0:08:58.13,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's actually a job to protect \Na very important client from assassins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:09:00.90,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,{\i1}A job battling assassins?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.39,0:09:04.92,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}If they end up on the same ship as me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.92,0:09:08.47,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}it'll add another layer of complexity \Nto the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.47,0:09:09.86,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.43,0:09:15.16,Default,Angel Anya,0,0,0,,We can't cause trouble for Mommy. \NForget about this ooting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:16.29,Default,Devil Anya,0,0,0,,Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:18.16,Default,Devil Anya,0,0,0,,I wanna relax on a big fancy boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.16,0:09:20.53,Default,Devil Anya,0,0,0,,You're thinking the exact same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.40,0:09:22.27,Default,Angel Anya,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.27,0:09:24.18,Default,Angel Anya,0,0,0,,If we go and help Mommy with her work,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.18,0:09:26.19,Default,Angel Anya,0,0,0,,we could kill two birds with one stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.02,0:09:31.43,Default,Devil Anya,0,0,0,,Be honest with yourself. \N You know you just want to go see the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:36.26,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Let me go on the boat! The big one!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.26,0:09:38.08,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Or I'm gonna go crazy! {K: literal is "turn into a delinquent", but this works. consider "throw a tantrum" as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.08,0:09:39.18,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, dear...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.47,0:09:43.69,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I'll ask my boss \Nif I can get some paid time off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.69,0:09:47.14,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Sure, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:47.90,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.35,0:09:51.48,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,I'll pull some strings so you can \Nget time off at the hospital, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.48,0:09:53.70,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Uh... Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.15,0:09:56.78,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,{\an8}Are you kidding me? \NI'm going to work you down to the bone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.55,0:10:01.73,Default,Senior Agent,0,0,0,,HQ may or may not be trying to cut \Nback on our shady overtime practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.73,0:10:02.08,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.54,0:10:06.09,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Well, little Anya's care and education \Nare part of Strix, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:08.86,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,Agent Twilight,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.86,0:10:12.54,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,I order you to execute a vacation\Nas skillfully as any other mission.{I order you to perfectly execute \Na type of mission called a vacation.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.98,0:10:19.47,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,An ooting! An ooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:23.11,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,It's been so long since I've had \Nan ooting with Mom and Dad!{Anya hasn't been on an ooting \Nwith Mama and Papa in forever.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:26.49,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,It has been a while, \Nthough I'm supposed to be on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.98,0:10:29.04,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,You'll fall out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:30.74,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}If not for this bodyguard job,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.74,0:10:33.99,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}the three of us could've enjoyed \Nthis vacation together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.22,0:10:37.15,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}What in the world am I saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.15,0:10:39.12,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I need to get my priorities straight! {K: consider "I need to get my priorities straight!"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.12,0:10:40.62,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.63,0:10:43.62,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\an8}Oh, we'll be getting off at the next stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.63,0:10:43.06,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}But maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:46.03,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.61,0:10:49.52,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}if this could be my last job...
Comment: 0,0:10:57.71,0:10:59.64,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.90,0:11:14.28,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,It's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.28,0:11:17.03,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Excited, excited, excited, excited, \Nexcited, excited, excited, excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.03,0:11:18.28,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:24.23,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Well, I have to meet up with my coworkers,\N so I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.84,0:11:27.04,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'll contact you when I get the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:29.65,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Sorry that you won't be able to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.65,0:11:31.18,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,You've got this, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.06,0:12:01.58,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,A pool!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.58,0:12:03.16,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,A circus!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:05.08,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,A game room!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:06.32,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.89,0:12:10.92,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,The ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.92,0:12:14.24,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Dad, this ship is so cool! \NThis feels like the start of a big adventure!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.24,0:12:17.42,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Well, this luxurious cruise ship\N is Ostania's pride and joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.42,0:12:19.21,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Let's hurry and go exploring!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:20.99,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,After we put our luggage in our room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:23.56,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Our own suite! So exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:33.65,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,It appears we've accidentally come \Nto the jail. This is the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.65,0:12:34.50,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,This is the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.50,0:12:36.82,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,This is what you're gonna \Nget down in third class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.12,0:12:41.07,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Please look forward to my grand \Nadventure in our next feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.07,0:12:44.00,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,You won this cruise in a raffle. \NDon't get greedy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.00,0:12:48.57,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,But this'll be my first bunkbed! \NI call the top bunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:49.83,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\an8}Do as you please. Just don't fall off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.17,0:12:52.78,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Yor and her company are probably \Nin the first-class rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.78,0:12:54.68,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Why does she get the good rooms?{No fair. Darn celebrities.}{K: btw she's calling yor a celebrity here (and not the other guests), but i like this change}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:12:57.11,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Well, she's here to do business, so... {K: should this be "she is"? or is it referring to yor and her coworkers? feels inconsistent with the previous line}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.85,0:12:59.84,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,Allow us to formally introduce ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:04.28,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I am Matthew McMahon, \Ndirector of policy at Berlint City Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.28,0:13:07.10,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,This is Heymann and Vides \Nfrom our business development team.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.50,0:13:08.95,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,And this is Forger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.91,0:13:14.53,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,I'm Furseal Grey, from the store development \Ngroup at Arhaus Department Stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:15.98,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,This is my wife, Shaty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:17.38,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about the kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.38,0:13:20.11,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Please! We want you and your family \Nto enjoy your time here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.55,0:13:24.58,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,If your wife needs any assistance whatsoever, \Nallow Forger to take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.58,0:13:25.52,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.37,0:13:29.37,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}So this is Ms. Olka from the Gretcher family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:31.63,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}She looks completely \Ndifferent from her picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.63,0:13:34.88,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I guess she had to change her appearance\Nto help her escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.94,0:13:34.88,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's a pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:36.09,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,{\an8}Pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:37.76,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,{\i1}So this is Ms. Olka's bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.76,0:13:39.88,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is she really capable enough for this job?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.88,0:13:42.75,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,This {\i1}Princess Lorelei{\i0} \Ncruise will be a short one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.75,0:13:46.39,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Three days and two nights, \Njust visiting the nearby islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.39,0:13:49.39,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,We hope you'll be able to relax \Nand enjoy this trip, Mr. Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.39,0:13:54.30,Default,Vides,0,0,0,,Though it's no department store, \Nthis ship does have a shopping mall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.30,0:13:56.07,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Would you like to go take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:59.45,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,{\i1}These two are just normal employees \Nwho don't know the truth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:00.19,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Sure, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.65,0:14:03.76,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I'm fine. I'll stay here with the baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.76,0:14:07.12,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,I see. Well, \N I'll have Forger stay behind to tend to your needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:10.23,Default,Heymann,0,0,0,,Right this way, Mr. Grey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.23,0:14:11.80,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Huh? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.25,0:14:17.17,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Is one bodyguard going to be enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.17,0:14:18.67,Default,Grey,0,0,0,,Shouldn't we all stay together?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.15,0:14:21.82,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,She should be quite safe in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.82,0:14:24.18,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,We will first be checking \Nthe rest of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.52,0:14:27.75,Default,Matthew,0,0,0,,You needn't worry. She is quite strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.78,0:14:37.27,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Your mission is to protect the sole survivors \Nof the tragedy: Olka and her son.
Comment: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:37.27,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,Olka and her son.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:42.21,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,We've received intel that the one pursuing her\N has several assassins on his side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.21,0:14:44.46,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,You are authorized to eliminate threats\Nby any means.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.46,0:14:46.68,Default,Shopkeeper,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Briar Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:50.84,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}They checked for signs of infiltration \Nand escape routes before we left,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:53.60,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}but I can't relax \Nuntil I check everything myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.60,0:14:56.29,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}Though, I'm sure the manager has also checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:15:01.49,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Huh, I guess you really are one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.49,0:15:03.56,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Huh? Uh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.56,0:15:04.38,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,One of who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.36,0:15:09.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Um, you are Olka, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.14,0:15:13.33,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I am. Though, I'd prefer \Nif you didn't use that name while we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.33,0:15:14.99,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh! I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:18.43,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Oh, did you wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:20.65,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm so terribly sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.65,0:15:22.92,Default,Gram,0,0,0,,Mama... Mama...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.21,0:15:26.56,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,It's so strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.62,0:15:31.77,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I look completely different, \Nbut he still knows that I'm his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.77,0:15:33.70,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Maybe it's because of my voice, my scent,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:36.33,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,or that his eyesight hasn't fully developed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.64,0:15:41.40,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I'm a little sad that I'll never hear\Nabout how much we look alike,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.40,0:15:43.51,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,but I guess I have bigger things to care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:47.15,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Besides, he looks like his father, \Nso it'd turn out the same either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.15,0:15:50.68,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Y-Your husband? \NHe seemed like a lovely person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.81,0:15:54.46,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,The man you just saw \Nis a member of our organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.46,0:15:57.60,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,He's just playing the part. \NHe is a good man, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.88,0:16:01.65,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,My husband was killed along \Nwith the rest of my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.33,0:16:05.69,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,My son is all I have left now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.56,0:16:08.76,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.76,0:16:12.03,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,It's fine. I guess it's just what happens\Nwhen you choose a life of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.69,0:16:15.20,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,But I've grown tired of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.73,0:16:17.86,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I don't need power or money.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:20.63,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I just want to live a quiet, peaceful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:30.93,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,There, there. What's got you so spooked?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.52,0:16:37.33,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Excuse me, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.33,0:16:39.52,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Can I be a bit selfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.38,0:16:44.96,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Ever since my family was killed, \NI've been forced to live in hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:47.28,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I'd like to spread my wings just a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:51.03,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I also want to give him a breath of fresh air. {K: "a breath of fresh air"? "let him breathe some fresh air"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.03,0:16:54.67,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,But we should really confer with the director first...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.67,0:16:56.65,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Please. Just for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.20,0:16:59.29,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,The ones after me don't know what I look like,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:03.04,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,nor should they know that I'm on this ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:07.05,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,And besides, I'll have you \Nto protect me, won't I?{And besides, you'll protect me if \Nit comes to that, won't you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.82,0:17:10.97,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,V-Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.97,0:17:12.74,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Just for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.04,0:17:21.70,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,If you keep acting that suspicious, \Nwon't you bring more attention to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.70,0:17:27.25,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Well, I'm looking out for the enemy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.56,0:17:30.81,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Your family is on this ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.81,0:17:34.07,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Yes, my husband and daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:38.13,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,Daddy! We need to hurry up and \Nexplore the ship before it sinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.13,0:17:40.08,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,It's not going to sink! \NStop scaring everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.25,0:17:42.25,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:45.04,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}This ship certainly is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.04,0:17:47.42,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}There seems to be quite a few celebrities present.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.69,0:17:49.60,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just in case of a terrorist incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.60,0:17:53.08,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}I should check for any suspicious people \Naboard and confirm the layout of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.08,0:17:55.91,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}I need to figure out who's meeting who,\N as well as where and when... {K: consider "figure out who's meeting who"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.91,0:17:57.69,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Daddy? {K:: not "daddy"?}{c:: note that i think it's fine to switch between them (dad and daddy) generally, as opposed to something like "papa" and "dad" or something. that might just be me though. feels a bit more versatile}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:00.47,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}Shit, I slipped into my usual habits!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.47,0:18:03.59,Default,Sylvia,0,0,0,,I order you to execute a vacation\Nas skillfully as any other mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.12,0:18:05.44,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.44,0:18:07.94,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,{\i1}I must try my hardest to enjoy my vacation \Nto the fullest!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:09.92,Default,Loid,0,0,0,,Why don't we go see a show?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:11.82,Default,Anya,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're always so serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.83,0:18:14.08,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.08,0:18:16.32,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,But why would you bring them with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.32,0:18:19.46,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't. It was all a complete coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:22.08,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,My family doesn't know about my real job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.41,0:18:24.71,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,So if a fight does happen to break out, {K:: consider "battle" -> "fight"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.71,0:18:26.97,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,it would be very inconvenient \Nif they were to spot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.97,0:18:30.45,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Actually, even having \Nany of the other guests see me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.45,0:18:32.18,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Well, if they're in third class,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.18,0:18:35.25,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,you probably won't see them \Nunless we go to a common area.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.25,0:18:36.60,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.60,0:18:38.85,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Sure, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.89,0:18:41.97,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,You seem really worried about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.97,0:18:44.13,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Aren't they just an alibi for the work you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.85,0:18:48.63,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.40,0:18:53.13,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I guess that's what they are.{c: im not sure if it "sounds" like she's saying this, but this is what the mangaTL had and i like it}{K: looks good to me. literal is just "i think you might be right"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.84,0:19:01.76,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Oh, of course! Let's go outside already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.76,0:19:03.32,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Oh, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.33,0:19:07.75,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I'll let you borrow this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.65,0:19:18.85,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,It feels so nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.60,0:19:25.85,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Um, this outfit...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:29.44,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Now we're just two moms enjoying the breeze.{Now we just look like two moms \Nwho came to enjoy the cruise.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.44,0:19:30.95,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,It's better than the suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.95,0:19:36.09,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,And if your husband sees you, he probably \Nwon't recognize you unless he's up close.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.09,0:19:37.67,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I guess you have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.21,0:19:43.14,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.87,0:19:46.23,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,What a nice, peaceful breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.63,0:19:54.13,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Wow, the shore is completely gone!{Wow, we can't see the shore at all anymore.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.55,0:19:56.71,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.09,0:20:03.47,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,There's so much I left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.68,0:20:11.89,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Oh, dear. Are you getting cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.40,0:20:13.69,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,I guess we can head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.89,0:20:18.07,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Um, Shaty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.29,0:20:22.88,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I-I'm going to give this my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.88,0:20:24.41,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'll make sure to protect...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.87,0:20:27.31,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I promise to properly do my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.91,0:20:30.18,Default,Gram,0,0,0,,Besh! Besh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.18,0:20:32.14,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Yes, I will do my very besht!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.21,0:20:35.42,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Gram.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:36.15,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.67,0:20:42.42,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,That's his name. Just like my father's. His real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:43.68,Default,Gram,0,0,0,,Dam!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.08,0:20:48.96,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,It's a pleasure to meet you, Gram!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.94,0:20:51.83,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,Want to hold him as we walk back?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.83,0:20:53.26,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,May I?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.26,0:20:55.32,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,{\i1}I need to make sure I don't break any of his bones!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.09,0:20:59.90,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry! I'll give him back to you, Shaty!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.82,0:21:03.73,Default,Guest (Woman),0,0,0,,{\an8}Hey, there's a show at five!
Comment: 0,0:21:02.42,0:21:03.72,Default,Guest (girl),0,0,0,,{\an8}Where's the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.73,0:21:05.08,Default,Guest (Man),0,0,0,,{\an8}Let's grab drinks at the bar upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.08,0:21:07.95,Default,Guest (Woman),0,0,0,,{\an8}Wow! You can even go shopping here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.70,0:21:07.95,Alt,Guest (Boy),0,0,0,,{\an8}Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.95,0:21:10.41,Default,Guest (Boy's father),0,0,0,,{\an8}What's the matter? Don't stray.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.41,0:21:13.71,Default,Guest (Man),0,0,0,,{\an8}I'm certain you will win the next election.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:13.71,Alt,Guest (Man),0,0,0,,{\an8}No, no, those stocks right now are—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.71,0:21:17.94,Default,Crew,0,0,0,,{\an8}Well, this isn't good. The lock to \Nthe emergency passage is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.57,0:21:20.30,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}I was almost forced to stay behind.
Comment: 0,0:21:19.33,0:21:20.30,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}That's why I told you not to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.62,0:21:22.19,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}This is so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.19,0:21:23.48,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}This company's products—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.48,0:21:25.59,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}So there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.59,0:21:27.39,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}E-226, all clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.39,0:21:29.20,Default,Crowd,0,0,0,,{\an8}What am I going to do with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.20,0:21:30.24,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,{\an8}Gram.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.88,0:21:34.72,Default,Olka,0,0,0,,{\an8}That's—name. Just like—father's.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:39.82,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,It's a—to meet you, Gram!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.45,0:21:44.38,Default,Yor,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry! I'll give him back to you, Shaty!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.38,0:21:46.33,Default,Informant,0,0,0,,Shaty, Shaty...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.33,0:21:50.56,Default,Informant,0,0,0,,Shaty Hutton, room 2125.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.56,0:21:54.60,Default,Informant,0,0,0,,Shaty Copeland, room 3064.
